### When to use which?
To help you decide which one to implement in your current project, consider this "Decision Tree":
| If the User Query is... | ...Use This Technique |
|---|---|
| **Short & Vague** (e.g., "Java threads") | **Expansion** (Add "virtual threads", "concurrency", "performance"). |
| **Multi-Part** (e.g., "Compare X and Y for Z") | **Decomposition** (Split into "How is X?", "How is Y?", "What is Z?"). |
| **Technical/Specific** (e.g., "Spring Boot 3.2 JIT optimization") | **HyDE** (Generate a "fake" technical answer to match against real docs). |
### Pro-Tip: Recursive Retrieval
If you are building a system to handle very large documents (like migration guides or technical manuals), you can combine **Decomposition** with **Recursive Character Splitting**. This ensures that once you break the question down, you are searching against chunks of text that are small enough to be precise, but large enough to keep their context.
